welcome.title: Get an API Key to authenticate you using Live Objects APIs
welcome.api-key:
API Keys are mandatory to authenticate your device or your application to Live Objects with MQTT or REST protocols.

The API keys that authenticate your account have certain rights.

Your keys must remain secret. We recommend you to use different API keys.

welcome.title: Create a FIFO to collect the messages of your devices
welcome.fifo-queue:
Your devices send their message to a FIFO in order to be used by an application.

Messages remain on your FIFO until an application retrieves them.

welcome.title: Create a routing key to fill a FIFO
welcome.route:
A routing key defines a rule for redirecting messages to a FIFO. e.g.

~event.v1.data.new.# : route all messages of all devices towards target FIFO

~event.v1.data.new.urn.lora.0004A3 : route all messages of device with devEUI 0004A3

modal.delete.label: Are you sure you want to delete these bindings?

new.title: Create new binding
new.routing_key_filter_description:

~event.v1.data.new.urn.lora.0004A3 : sends all messages of device with devEUI 0004A3

registration.cnil:
Under article 32 of the French Law No 78-17 of January 6th, 1978, we inform you that personal identifiable information collected by Live Objects is processed.
The Data Controller is Orange Applications for Business.
The purpose for data processing is, on the one hand, get your feedbacks on the service and on the other exchange on your needs and our solutions.
Personal identifiable information that has been processed is kept for the duration of the subscription.
Pursuant to articles 38 et seq. of the aforementioned law, you have rights of access, rectification and opposition. To assert these rights, you can contact Orange Applications for Business at OAB-DonneesPersonnelles@list.orange.com or by post at the following address:
OAB - Personal Data
Department for Quality, Process & Security (DQPS)
4 rue de la Châtaigneraie
35510 Cesson-Sévigné (France)
